01:38:17,172 --> 01:38:19,052
Hey, come on.
Wouldn't any man feel

1482
01:38:19,053 --> 01:38:20,776
guilty if his wife was suicidal?

1483
01:38:20,809 --> 01:38:24,045
Yeah. So maybe she took
the sleeping pills

1484
01:38:24,079 --> 01:38:26,448
with the intention
of killing herself.

1485
01:38:26,482 --> 01:38:29,885
But how did she end up
lying on a marble floor

1486
01:38:29,918 --> 01:38:32,420
in a freezing bathroom with her
head under the toilet bowl?

1487
01:38:32,921 --> 01:38:34,422
How about this?

1488
01:39:22,638 --> 01:39:24,472
Sunny wakes up miserable.

1489
01:39:29,678 --> 01:39:32,480
Second marriage is over,
children are leaving home.

1490
01:39:33,815 --> 01:39:35,517
What's to live for?

1491
01:41:48,216 --> 01:41:49,666
But when she was found, her

1492
01:41:49,667 --> 01:41:51,653
nightgown was hiked
over her waist.

1493
01:41:51,687 --> 01:41:55,857
Exactly. How did it get there?

1494
01:41:55,891 --> 01:41:59,828
Okay, let's say she's standing
at the sink. She has to pee.

1495
01:41:59,861 --> 01:42:03,331
At exactly the same
instant, the drugs hit,

1496
01:42:03,364 --> 01:42:07,202
her body convulses, she
grabs the nightgown.

1497
01:42:11,406 --> 01:42:14,810
- I don't buy that.
- It does seem far-fetched.

1498
01:42:14,843 --> 01:42:17,045
- Well, so is the truth sometimes.
- Oh, bull.

1499
01:42:17,078 --> 01:42:19,114
I think she took the
barbiturates the previous night.

1500
01:42:19,147 --> 01:42:22,684
And, let's say, he
saw her take them.

1501
01:42:22,818 --> 01:42:26,321
Or she told him she was going
to before they fell asleep.

1502
01:42:34,830 --> 01:42:37,265
This time, he wants
her to succeed.

1503
01:42:47,843 --> 01:42:49,010
Sunny?

1504
01:43:16,204 --> 01:43:18,406
Maybe there's some way
he can help her along.

1505
01:43:19,975 --> 01:43:22,878
Of course. The open window.

1506
01:43:23,879 --> 01:43:25,313
Zero degrees.

1507
01:43:26,882 --> 01:43:29,751
But somebody might see her there.

1508
01:43:29,885 --> 01:43:33,054
The action of dragging her would
naturally pull up the nightgown.

1509
01:44:03,418 --> 01:44:06,454
In this cold, how long
could she survive?

1510
01:44:26,875 --> 01:44:29,577
Remember what Sunny said?

1511
01:44:29,610 --> 01:44:33,815
"I would've been better off.
You would've been better off."

1512
01:44:38,987 --> 01:44:41,489
because the law is a
blunt instrument.

1513
01:44:41,522 --> 01:44:45,426
It is not a rapier.
It is a cudgel.

1514
01:44:45,460 --> 01:44:47,268
Tomorrow, death penalty. Which

1515
01:44:47,269 --> 01:44:49,497
reminds me of the
comedian who said

1516
01:44:49,530 --> 01:44:51,833
"I don't know why they
call it the death penalty?

1517
01:44:51,900 --> 01:44:54,102
"It's no penalty. You're
out of the game."

1518
01:45:03,211 --> 01:45:04,612
- Good news.
- Great news.

1519
01:45:04,645 --> 01:45:06,114
And more good news.

1520
01:45:06,147 --> 01:45:08,349
- The decision came down?
- They just announced it.

1521
01:45:08,383 --> 01:45:11,019
- Five-zip.
- We murdered them.

1522
01:45:11,052 --> 01:45:12,052
Grounds?

1523
01:45:12,053 --> 01:45:13,454
Well, they got the
Brillhoffer notes.

1524
01:45:13,488 --> 01:45:16,357
And that silly-silly, guilty-man's
argument, search and seizure.

1525
01:45:16,391 --> 01:45:18,293
- Federal or state?
- Both.

1526
01:45:18,326 --> 01:45:20,862
Yeah, if it's federal, they could
appeal at US Supreme Court,

1527
01:45:20,996 --> 01:45:22,864
but because it's Rhode
Island, they can't. We win.

1528
01:45:24,232 --> 01:45:26,868
Don't get too excited till
we see Brillhoffer's notes.

1529
01:45:27,035 --> 01:45:28,536
We destroyed their medical case,

1530
01:45:28,569 --> 01:45:30,480
but their witnesses
still carry emotional

1531
01:45:30,481 --> 01:45:32,073
weight if there is a second trial.

1532
01:45:32,107 --> 01:45:34,073
Unless the Brillhoffer notes show

1533
01:45:34,074 --> 01:45:36,277
that they've changed
their stories.

1534
01:45:38,013 --> 01:45:39,614
Good afternoon, sir.

1535
01:45:41,249 --> 01:45:43,851
- Let me get that for you.
- Thank you.

1536
01:45:58,033 --> 01:46:00,668
- You have Brillhoffer's notes?
- Yes.

1537
01:46:00,701 --> 01:46:02,904
- Well?
- They're not what we hoped.

1538
01:46:03,071 --> 01:46:04,239
I knew it.

1539
01:46:07,375 --> 01:46:09,110
They're much better.

1540
01:46:11,046 --> 01:46:12,819
No one mentioned
seeing insulin when

1541
01:46:12,820 --> 01:46:14,449
they first talked to Brillhoffer.

1542
01:46:14,482 --> 01:46:17,953
Plus, Maria told him
that, at Thanksgiving,

1543
01:46:17,986 --> 01:46:20,221
when she supposedly first saw
insulin for the first time,

1544
01:46:20,255 --> 01:46:24,359
she couldn't even read any of the
labels. They were all scraped off.

1545
01:46:24,392 --> 01:46:26,928
- What does this mean?
- It means,

1546
01:46:27,062 --> 01:46:28,129
that if there is a second trial,

1547
01:46:28,163 --> 01:46:30,231
we can be reasonably confident.

1548
01:46:30,265 --> 01:46:33,935
Both the medical case and their
witnesses are now highly suspect.

1549
01:46:34,102 --> 01:46:35,102
Ah.

1550
01:46:56,457 --> 01:46:59,594
Darling, this is Alan Dershowitz.

1551
01:47:00,295 --> 01:47:02,130
Yes, I know. Hello.

1552
01:47:02,163 --> 01:47:05,933
Alan tells me... Well,
things look very hopeful.

1553
01:47:07,768 --> 01:47:10,305
I knew it would come out
all right. Thank you.

1554
01:47:14,642 --> 01:47:17,678
Yes, Alan, thank you. I
am eternally grateful.

1555
01:47:17,712 --> 01:47:19,747
Hey, this means we'll be
getting back your bail.

1556
01:47:19,780 --> 01:47:21,983
A million dollars.

1557
01:47:22,017 --> 01:47:24,052
I know I still owe you, Alan.

1558
01:47:25,620 --> 01:47:27,622
Please send me your bill.

1559
01:47:28,623 --> 01:47:30,491
And maybe when you're in New York

1560
01:47:30,525 --> 01:47:35,997
we can meet for lunch.
I'd enjoy that.

1561
01:47:36,164 --> 01:47:39,400
One thing, Claus. Legally,
this was an important victory.

1562
01:47:40,468 --> 01:47:42,637
Morally, you're on your own.

1563
01:47:55,316 --> 01:47:57,793
Claus von Bulow was given a second

1564
01:47:57,794 --> 01:48:00,488
trial and acquitted
on both counts.

1565
01:48:03,058 --> 01:48:07,662
This is all you can know,
all you can be told.

1566
01:48:09,164 --> 01:48:13,000
When you get where I am,
you will know the rest.

1567
01:48:46,201 --> 01:48:48,469
Two packs of Vantage, please.

1568
01:48:56,411 --> 01:49:00,415
- Anything else?
- Yes, a phial of insulin.

1569
01:49:07,822 --> 01:49:09,224
Just kidding.
